ons. Two papers focus on rate regulation in the auto insurance industry, and provide broad overviews of the structure and economics of the insurance industry as a whole. Also addressed are the system of regulating insurance companies in the United States, who insures the insurers, and the effects of tax law changes in the 1980s on the prices of insurance policies.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aBusiness. 0aCasualty insurancexUnited States. 0aCasualty insurancezUnited States. 0aCasualty insurance. 0aProperty insurancexUnited States. 0aProperty insurancezUnited States. 0aProperty insurance. 0aSocial sciences. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh1 aBradford, David F., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2015z978311063538640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226070322423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226070322.jpg  a978-3-11-063538-6  University of Chicago Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles